<item>
            <title>[LU-3662] Allow reading from ldlm.dump_namespaces or new ldlm.namespaces.*.dump_locks file</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-3662</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Imperative lock dumping via writes to /proc/fs/lustre/ldlm/dump_namespaces only works once every 10 seconds because of the rate limitation imposed by ns_next_dump. Since ldlm_expired_completion_wait() has it&apos;s own 5 minute rate limit, it seems best just to do away with ns_next_dump altogether.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It would also be nice if we had a per namespace dump trigger and if we could just cat that file to get the dump rather than having to get it from the logs.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
